cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

The paper presents a proof-of-concept for automated grapevine phenotyping using convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and image segmentation. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves training the CNN using ground truth annotations, which suggests the involvement of machine learning techniques. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the second most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of adaptive software, which suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) the third most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of sensors and monitoring, which suggests the involvement of information retrieval techniques, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) the fourth most likely sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) the fifth most likely sub-category.
